1
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:51,801
FRANKLY SPEAKING

2
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:55,472
Park Jin-bok!

3
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:58,516
Have you lost your mind?

4
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,976
Hey! Forget about the shoot.

5
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,312
Get this psycho out of my sight!

6
00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:03,313
Get your act together!

7
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:05,315
Everyone you see right now
is here to work.

8
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:07,567
No one came here to be harassed!

9
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:08,651
You rude bastard!

10
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:09,861
Mr. Song Ki-baek!

11
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:18,286
-What is this?
-What?

12
00:01:18,369 --> 00:01:21,539
What… What's happening?

13
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:25,251
-This can't be happening. It can't be.
-Have you lost your mind?

14
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:26,753
No, no way.

15
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:30,006
Unbelievable. He just went
and bit his head off.

16
00:01:30,089 --> 00:01:31,466
What is he, a shark?

17
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:33,718
This is all a lie!

18
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:36,888
EPISODE 2: SHARK IN A POOL

19
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:47,357
Currently, the KOSPI stands
at 2,697.58 points,

20
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:51,486
marking a decrease of 9.44 points
from the previous trading session.

21
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:54,197
Meanwhile, the KOSDAQ
is showing a slight uptick,

22
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:57,534
rising by 0.66 points
to reach 923.62 points.

23
00:01:58,827 --> 00:01:59,786
No, I'm not.

24
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:01,788
-Hey. You can't stand me, right?
-Yes!

25
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:04,040
I'll chew that jerk to pieces today…

26
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:05,333
Get your act together!

27
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:11,714
A non-soft cookie from the land
of non-soft cookies wanted to become

28
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:14,926
a soft cookie and traveled to the land
of soft cookies.

29
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:17,762
The gatekeeper of the soft cookie land
said, "Hey, kid, today…"

30
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:19,472
Just one slap in the face from me,

31
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:20,849
and you'll turn over a new leaf.

32
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:23,476
You rude bastard!

33
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,938
Why on earth did he do that?

34
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:28,273
It is truly hard to believe.

35
00:02:28,356 --> 00:02:31,651
Let's hear from Mr. Song Ki-baek
who was at the scene.

36
00:02:31,734 --> 00:02:32,902
Just why…

37
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:36,239
Why in God's name

38
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:43,913
did you speak your thoughts out loud?

39
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:48,585
A CLEAN BODY
LEADS TO A HEALTHY MIND

40
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:06,436
Time to get to work
so Mr. Kim can tear me a new one.

41
00:03:07,645 --> 00:03:09,439
What did I just say?

42
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:11,816
Man, what's wrong with me?

43
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:15,904
That Song Ki-baek. Song Ki-baek!

44
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:18,072
Let's recap. So what happened was--

45
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:23,870
Song Ki-baek tore into PN
with both verbal and non-verbal violence.

46
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:27,749
PN now claims to be suffering
from extremely severe PTSD as a result

47
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:30,877
and has provided a doctor's note stating
he can no longer be in our show.

48
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:34,005
What are the chances
of PN coming back after recovery?

49
00:03:34,088 --> 00:03:36,049
He wants to gracefully leave the show.

50
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:37,091
Oh, yeah?

51
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:40,094
Then we should also
gracefully leave the show.

52
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:41,346
I'll go talk to PN.

53
00:03:41,971 --> 00:03:44,349
We can't afford to be graceful like him.

54
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:46,601
We have to be pathetic
and beg him to stay.

55
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:49,520
-I'll come with you.
-No thanks.

56
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:51,564
You stay here
and take care of what you can.

57
00:03:52,857 --> 00:03:54,234
Maybe I should go like this.

58
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:56,653
I've been crawling
and begging to so many people.

59
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:01,449
Don't try too hard.

60
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:03,743
How can I not?

61
00:04:03,826 --> 00:04:05,536
The crew might lose their jobs.

62
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:08,623
I'll crawl if that's what it takes.

63
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:11,668
Hey, Song Ki-baek! Song…

64
00:04:11,751 --> 00:04:13,670
Where is he? Where's that bastard?

65
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:15,171
Has he run away? Where's…

66
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,297
Where is Song Ki-baek?

67
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:18,841
Yoon Ji-hu! Where is that bastard?

68
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:21,344
I'm going to kill him and go to hell.
Bring him to me.

69
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:23,638
I've got a shoot
for Pyororong Witch School.

70
00:04:23,721 --> 00:04:24,847
Huh? You have what?

71
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:25,974
A shoot, sir.

72
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:28,518
Hey, you little… Take that thing off.

73
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:30,061
Hey! Where's Song Ki-baek…

74
00:04:30,144 --> 00:04:32,647
Tell me where he… Hey!

75
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:33,773
Mr. Kim is throwing a fit.

76
00:04:33,856 --> 00:04:35,984
Don't come here. Hide somewhere for a bit.

77
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,987
"Don't come here"? "Hide somewhere"?

78
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,488
Oh, man. What am I going to do?

79
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,534
Oh, he's calling me. What do I do?

80
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:48,705
It's been a while. Taking a smoke break?

81
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:53,293
Hey, Ki-baek doesn't smoke.
He's doing the anti-smoking campaign.

82
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:54,294
Oh, wow.

83
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:56,337
It's only been a week or so
since I quit.

84
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:02,760
You smell like an ashtray.
Please take care of that.

85
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,888
No, I didn't mean that. I…

86
00:05:07,682 --> 00:05:09,225
NO MORE STINKY BREATH!

87
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:19,736
Wow. He's thoughtfully rude.

88
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:23,948
Hey, Ki-baek!

89
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:26,659
Mr. Kim is looking for you
with lasers shooting out of his eyes.

90
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:27,994
What's going on?

91
00:05:28,077 --> 00:05:30,038
Hold on, wait. Are you free?

92
00:05:30,121 --> 00:05:32,790
-Can you fill in for me for a dubbing job?
-Don't do that.

93
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:34,042
Oh, no, sir.

94
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,335
What?

95
00:05:36,377 --> 00:05:37,670
Don't worry, man.

96
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:39,839
-I'll talk to them and make sure--
-No!

97
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:42,842
All you do is talk trash about people.

98
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:45,136
Do you think I don't know how
you pass off tiresome tasks

99
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:49,682
to your juniors and then gripe
about them doing a crappy job.

100
00:05:52,393 --> 00:05:53,686
Ki-baek, I have a favor to ask.

101
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:56,564
No favors.

102
00:05:56,647 --> 00:05:58,399
No! No more favors!

103
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:01,069
And no more green juice!

104
00:06:25,968 --> 00:06:28,304
Enjoying a cup of tea with my heart.

105
00:06:28,387 --> 00:06:31,390
Happiness comes from these little moments.

106
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:34,560
I'm hungry.

107
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:40,942
Did you know? It's already corn season.

108
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:43,194
-Huh?
-The hairdresser downstairs gave me some.

109
00:06:44,028 --> 00:06:44,904
Aren't they huge?

110
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:46,739
Come on, I don't want corn.

111
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:48,199
Let's order in, Mom.

112
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:53,329
-How about Yupdduk?
-Oh! Order a super spicy one!

113
00:06:53,412 --> 00:06:56,666
You have no problem ordering delivery
when you don't even make a penny.

114
00:06:58,376 --> 00:06:59,460
The corn is nice and chewy.

115
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:02,088
I'm in pain, so Yupdduk?

116
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,048
-Come on, Yupdduk.
-Knock it off.

117
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:05,800
I'm going to the gym.

118
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:08,010
Didn't you say today was your day off?

119
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,846
You teach people how to work out,

120
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,223
and you want to work out
on your day off too?

121
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:13,141
Oh, stop it.

122
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:15,393
I've got to work out myself
because it's my day off.

123
00:07:15,476 --> 00:07:17,228
Come on, Mom. Let's have Yupdduk.

124
00:07:17,311 --> 00:07:19,063
I'll make you rice cake soup for dinner.

125
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:20,106
It isn't the same.

126
00:07:20,189 --> 00:07:21,691
Hey!

127
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:22,942
See you later.

128
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:25,111
You're taking all the eggs again?

129
00:07:25,194 --> 00:07:27,697
I peeled them to make jangjorim.

130
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:32,034
Goodness! Let me get you some cold water.

131
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,035
Oh, forget it.

132
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:37,081
Didn't you notice it's steaming hot?
Maybe you need glasses.

133
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:38,291
Oh, please.

134
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,084
You good-for-nothing.

135
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:43,588
You're staring at your phone
when your mom's tongue is on fire?

136
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:47,091
No way. Mom, Dad. Look at this.

137
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:51,929
IDOL SINGER P
ASSAULTED BY ANNOUNCER S

138
00:07:53,931 --> 00:07:55,308
It's not too bad, right?

139
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:57,101
This works best when you want to hide.

140
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,729
So what happened anyway?

141
00:07:59,812 --> 00:08:03,316
Why'd you do something so wild that it
made the news and made Mr. Kim flip out?

142
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:08,112
Why do you keep making the news
instead of reporting it?

143
00:08:08,196 --> 00:08:09,822
Oh, whatever. Stop asking questions.

144
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:12,200
How do you film in this thing?

145
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:13,326
I can't breathe.

146
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:14,994
You get used to it.

147
00:08:15,077 --> 00:08:18,331
I even ran around in the hospital
with Sol yesterday wearing this.

148
00:08:18,414 --> 00:08:21,083
-She's back in the hospital?
-Just for a few days for some tests.

149
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:22,919
Sol is fine.

150
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:24,504
You should worry about yourself.

151
00:08:25,922 --> 00:08:28,925
Are you planning on going freelance?

152
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,885
Trying to leave
while you're in the limelight?

153
00:08:30,968 --> 00:08:32,053
That's ridiculous!

154
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:34,430
It's not that.

155
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:35,515
All right then.

156
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,809
I'd better get to the shoot
for "Pororong."

157
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:41,103
"Pyo-ro-rong."

158
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:42,563
What's your problem?

159
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:46,025
It's "pyororong"
as in Pyororong Witch School,

160
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:49,028
not "pororong"
as in Pororo the Little Penguin.

161
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:50,696
Can't you say "pyo" instead of "po"?

162
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:52,490
Fine.

163
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:55,785
I'm off to shoot Pyororong Witch School.

164
00:08:57,703 --> 00:08:59,038
I'll take this with me.

165
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:11,342
ANNOUNCER S
CAUSES SCENE DURING SHOOT

166
00:09:12,593 --> 00:09:15,221
This is obviously me.

167
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:18,432
Oh, she…

168
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,726
WRITER ON WOO-JU

169
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:25,314
Why won't you answer your phone?

170
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:28,776
Because I don't want to.

171
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:31,487
JBC NEWS AT NOON

172
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,864
Mr. Song Ki-baek, please come with me.

173
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,866
All I can do is just beg PN to stay,

174
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,035
but you're the one who caused all this.

175
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:40,329
If we lose PN,
it'll be the end of our show.

176
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:42,290
The jerk is the one who should apologize.

177
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,083
Are you really going to be like this?

178
00:09:45,334 --> 00:09:47,211
I understand your logic, Ms. On.

179
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:49,338
Considering his influence,

180
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:52,341
I agree that this is an issue
that must be solved.

181
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,384
So you get it.

182
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,261
The hell I do!

183
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:05,187
Did you not know PN was a horrible person
who treats people like crap?

184
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:06,480
There's no way you didn't.

185
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:11,402
You just pretended not to and enjoyed
the free stuff and advertisers he brought.

186
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:13,487
Is it okay to be an ass if you're a star?

187
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:18,117
What else can we do?

188
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:21,746
You think we can just be like,
"Well, he got what he deserved."

189
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:24,832
Look, the entire crew's livelihood
is at stake here.

190
00:10:24,915 --> 00:10:26,667
Don't talk like this is a simple matter.

191
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:28,544
I'm not. It's hard for me to say this.

192
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:31,297
But I can't apologize to him.

193
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:35,843
Mr. Song Ki-baek.
You're really not going to apologize?

194
00:10:35,926 --> 00:10:39,722
It's not that I won't. I really can't.

195
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:41,349
Right now, I'm in a state…

196
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,353
-What do you mean?
-Back off!

197
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:47,188
The doors are closing.

198
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:52,360
What am I going to do?

199
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:53,861
What do I do about this?

200
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:02,411
Wow. Was I wrong about you?

201
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:03,537
Ki-baek, seriously!

202
00:11:03,621 --> 00:11:05,623
Hey, is something going on with you?

203
00:11:05,706 --> 00:11:08,834
I never thought you, of all people,
would do something like this.

204
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:11,921
Have you always had trouble
controlling your emotions?

205
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:14,090
KIM SANG-JIN

206
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:15,007
KIM JERK

207
00:11:15,091 --> 00:11:16,217
Say something!

208
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:21,555
Don't break the absolute rules

209
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:24,308
Don't let go of my hand

210
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:26,060
Unity is my weapon

211
00:11:26,143 --> 00:11:28,187
Walk towards the wilderness

212
00:11:28,729 --> 00:11:30,314
I know that's your home ground

213
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:32,108
Stand up to the threat

214
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:33,442
Push past it, push past it!

215
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:35,945
I'm listening, sir.

216
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:38,739
Get it together, man.

217
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:40,783
Just go for now.

218
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:43,452
Hey, Song Ki-baek.

219
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:47,581
That's him, guys.

220
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:50,334
Hey, you're the one who attacked
my sweet PN, right?

221
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:51,585
Let's kick his ass!

222
00:11:51,669 --> 00:11:53,879
-You, apologize to him!
-Come on, guys!

223
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,965
-Hey!
-Hey!

224
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:00,052
What?

225
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:02,805
-There he is!
-Hey!

226
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:05,808
That's Ki-baek. Hi, Ki-baek.

227
00:12:05,891 --> 00:12:07,309
-We meet again.
-Come out here.

228
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:09,520
-Get out of the car!
-Watch out, guys.

229
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:13,065
God.

230
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:17,820
Man, seriously.

231
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:19,238
HANGUK MILK

232
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:24,285
You've got to have
strawberry milk with soju.

233
00:12:24,368 --> 00:12:29,123
Jesus. I have better things to do
than fetch you milk, you know.

234
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,250
Those jerks.

235
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:33,294
They wouldn't even let you see him?

236
00:12:33,377 --> 00:12:38,132
I waited two hours in front of PN's agency
and three hours in front of his house.

237
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:42,803
You should've known
when to give up and leave.

238
00:12:42,887 --> 00:12:44,388
Man, you're an idiot.

239
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:45,931
Think our show will be canceled?

240
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,266
It's already been canceled.

241
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:50,019
They made the final decision just now.

242
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:51,437
We need to leave the office.

243
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:54,857
To be honest, I've always felt guilty.

244
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:58,194
Every time we heard PN yelling
at the staff and saw them crying,

245
00:12:59,403 --> 00:13:01,030
we pretended like we didn't see it.

246
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:04,033
Well, what could we have done?

247
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:06,785
Fly at his throat like Song Ki-baek did?

248
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:09,497
We might not have been able
to fly at his throat,

249
00:13:10,164 --> 00:13:12,208
but if this is how
things were going to turn out,

250
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:18,047
perhaps I shouldn't have lashed out
at Song Ki-baek to make him apologize.

251
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:35,314
PHONE
CONTACTS

252
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:42,238
MOM

253
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:00,548
We're human, just like them.

254
00:14:01,549 --> 00:14:04,969
If they play dirty, we have the right
to defend ourselves.

255
00:14:05,052 --> 00:14:06,303
But still…

256
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:09,807
BEAUTY MANAGER NA YU-JEONG

257
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,142
Don't worry. I'll take care of the rest.

258
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:20,359
My goodness.

259
00:14:20,442 --> 00:14:24,113
Sweetheart. What on earth is going on?

260
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:25,281
Did you get my text?

261
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,116
You're not hurt anywhere, are you?

262
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:31,745
You won't even say hello to your brother?

263
00:14:31,829 --> 00:14:32,872
Hey, man.

264
00:14:40,796 --> 00:14:41,630
What's this?

265
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:46,385
LET ME STAY HERE TONIGHT

266
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:54,518
It may be uncomfortable,
but you'll have to make do.

267
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:56,103
I'll clear out the room in the morning.

268
00:14:58,314 --> 00:14:59,899
What's up with Ki-baek?

269
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:02,443
What do you think?
You saw the news, didn't you?

270
00:15:02,526 --> 00:15:06,113
"Mr. S who assaulted an idol." That's him.

271
00:15:06,196 --> 00:15:09,700
People may not know,
but I recognized him right away.

272
00:15:09,783 --> 00:15:12,161
Because they did a crappy job
blurring out his face.

273
00:15:12,244 --> 00:15:13,704
My poor Ki-baek.

274
00:15:13,787 --> 00:15:15,831
He just went in there
without saying a word.

275
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,626
He must be feeling terrible.

276
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:20,044
Oh, boy.

277
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:24,715
But he's supposed to give me
my allowance today.

278
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:27,426
Can I ask for just another 100,000 won?

279
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:28,552
Are you kidding?

280
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:30,679
Don't you dare say a word.

281
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:35,017
I have to ask him for money
for our living expenses today.

282
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:45,986
Ki-baek, wake up.

283
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:48,739
Hey. Come out here for a second.

284
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:50,741
What…

285
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,161
What are you doing?

286
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:59,083
I know you're going through
something at work,

287
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:03,462
but why would you just drop in like this?
You're making everyone tiptoe around you.

288
00:16:03,545 --> 00:16:05,255
What are you doing? Stop it.

289
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:06,966
Huh? For God's sake,

290
00:16:07,049 --> 00:16:09,468
take off the mask!

291
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:12,638
What the heck?

292
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:15,265
Have you gone crazy?

293
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:18,435
Ki-baek. What's going on with you?

294
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:22,272
Ouch! That must hurt.

295
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:23,649
Ki-baek.

296
00:16:23,732 --> 00:16:25,818
I don't know what happened,

297
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:27,611
but let's sit down and talk.

298
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:28,904
Oh, for God's sake!

299
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:31,490
Just leave me alone, will you?

300
00:16:31,573 --> 00:16:34,034
I don't need your consolation. Okay?

301
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:35,536
Don't treat me any differently.

302
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:37,538
You wouldn't even care if I died.

303
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:40,124
All you care about
is the money I give you.

304
00:16:40,207 --> 00:16:43,210
Ki-baek! If that's how you're going to be,
go back in there.

305
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:48,632
Just leave me the hell alone!

306
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:50,217
Damn it.

307
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:52,928
You've never bothered to visit us before.

308
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:55,389
You're only here
because you've got nowhere to go.

309
00:16:55,472 --> 00:16:57,307
And you don't pay
for everything around here.

310
00:16:57,391 --> 00:16:58,892
Don't be so patronizing about--

311
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:00,519
What? Patronizing?

312
00:17:00,602 --> 00:17:02,521
What? Am I wrong?

313
00:17:02,604 --> 00:17:04,940
You've always acted like
you're the only adult!

314
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:08,235
You're a 30-year-old man
who's barely making ends meet,

315
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:10,029
so don't you preach to me!

316
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,697
What? You little…

317
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,157
Enough!

318
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:20,456
Stop it. That's enough.

319
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:17,221
Hey.

320
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:19,598
You actually came.

321
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:21,725
You told me to.

322
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:23,727
Still, I didn't think you'd show up,

323
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:26,188
especially after bolting
like that earlier.

324
00:18:27,648 --> 00:18:29,316
So did you meet with PN?

325
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:32,111
He wouldn't see me.

326
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:34,530
I waited five hours.

327
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:40,285
Listen, Ms. On Woo-ju.

328
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:41,578
Thank you.

329
00:18:43,038 --> 00:18:47,334
I've wished at least a hundred times
that I could punch PN.

330
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:53,090
I knew all about how he only bullied
the young and powerless staff members.

331
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:57,094
I'm the head writer,

332
00:18:57,177 --> 00:19:03,350
but all I did was tell them to let it go
and I'd talk to him later.

333
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:11,275
Anyway, thanks for beating him up
when I couldn't.

334
00:19:11,358 --> 00:19:12,901
"Beat him up"? I didn't…

335
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:18,073
You totally beat him up with your words,
and it felt great to see that.

336
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,075
Are you always like that?

337
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:22,494
I mean, is that okay? You're an anchor.

338
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:26,540
No, I'm not always like that.

339
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:29,877
It's been driving me totally crazy
since yesterday.

340
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:33,046
Yesterday?

341
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:36,300
Hey, hang on.

342
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:40,262
Wash it down with this.

343
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:42,306
Oh, I'm good.

344
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:43,265
Just try it.

345
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:45,726
Bitter and sweet,
they're a perfect pair. Here.

346
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:53,150
I'm not drunk, you know.

347
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:55,402
I hope not.

348
00:19:55,485 --> 00:19:57,613
I'm telling you. I'm not drunk.

349
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:20,552
You're going to sleep out here?

350
00:20:20,636 --> 00:20:22,512
Come on, you'll get in a lot of trouble.

351
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:26,433
Listen. Give me your address.
I'll call you a cab.

352
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:30,771
Okay? Your address.

353
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,192
Oh, boy.

354
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:24,992
She'll be all right.

355
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:29,496
She can't expect me
to stay with her all night.

356
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:35,627
I'll be going then.

357
00:21:37,504 --> 00:21:38,755
Excuse me.

358
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:43,677
Shouldn't we film a final episode?

359
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:46,847
The show's been on for two years.
We should say goodbye to the viewers.

360
00:21:47,848 --> 00:21:49,474
People don't do that anymore.

361
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:51,852
Our ratings have been down
for a while now.

362
00:21:51,935 --> 00:21:54,229
Let's just accept
that this is the end of it.

363
00:21:54,771 --> 00:21:55,939
Let's start on the next one.

364
00:21:57,899 --> 00:21:59,818
-Your greenroom is this way.
-Okay.

365
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:02,279
See? My greenroom is upstairs. Come here.

366
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:04,197
What is it?

367
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:06,074
What's up with them?

368
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:09,119
One of their cast screwed up,
and their show is being canceled.

369
00:22:09,202 --> 00:22:10,329
No way.

370
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:12,080
-It's true.
-What?

371
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:15,876
I hear this was their first show.
They probably won't get another chance.

372
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:19,296
You should be careful too. Okay?

373
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:21,048
-I'll see you upstairs.
-Yeah, yeah.

374
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:32,726
I respect you…

375
00:22:34,061 --> 00:22:34,978
No, I don't.

376
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:37,898
Let's try one syllable at a time.

377
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:40,525
This is

378
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:43,737
so damn stressful.

379
00:22:47,365 --> 00:22:49,701
Man. I'm sorry.

380
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:56,041
Everything was

381
00:22:56,792 --> 00:22:58,293
not my fault.

382
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:02,339
That's right. It wasn't all my fault.

383
00:23:04,591 --> 00:23:07,260
It seems I can't bring myself
to say what I don't mean,

384
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:09,387
which is just ridiculous.

385
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,768
MR. KIM

386
00:23:15,352 --> 00:23:18,230
Don't be so upset about it, all right?

387
00:23:18,313 --> 00:23:22,859
You were going to leave News at Noon
to audition for the main news show anyway.

388
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:27,030
Just think of this as a little break.

389
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:30,325
Here, you want candy?

390
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:35,163
By the way, I just don't understand
no matter how hard I try.

391
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:36,414
Why did you do that?

392
00:23:36,498 --> 00:23:38,166
This isn't your first day on the job.

393
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:39,709
With your experience,

394
00:23:39,793 --> 00:23:42,838
I'm sure you know better than
to cause a scene in public.

395
00:23:42,921 --> 00:23:46,341
You're not like the other guys
who get into trouble for their temper.

396
00:23:46,424 --> 00:23:49,052
I wouldn't be so curious
if it was anybody else.

397
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:51,012
I just can't help wondering.

398
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:54,182
Damn.

399
00:23:54,808 --> 00:23:56,977
Oh! Hey, the brand awards.

400
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:58,353
You should host it.

401
00:23:58,436 --> 00:24:01,064
Park Jin-u was supposed to do it,
but he was in a car accident.

402
00:24:01,648 --> 00:24:03,650
They wanted me
to get back to them by today,

403
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:04,776
and you're not busy.

404
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:07,028
You'll be taking a long break.

405
00:24:07,529 --> 00:24:09,823
Since you're taking a break,
do this for me.

406
00:24:09,906 --> 00:24:11,491
Okay! Good.

407
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:15,036
Take a nice, long break, okay?
Just take a break and think.

408
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:19,624
Use this break to reflect on yourself
and really use your brain, you know.

409
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:21,626
Why do you keep calling it a break?

410
00:24:22,711 --> 00:24:25,380
I'll still have to come to work
where you breathe down my neck.

411
00:24:25,463 --> 00:24:27,799
It's a punishment.
You'll dump all the menial jobs on me.

412
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:29,676
Excuse me?

413
00:24:29,759 --> 00:24:31,887
Also, did you step in poop
on your way here?

414
00:24:31,970 --> 00:24:33,763
-Poop?
-Don't you know your feet stink?

415
00:24:39,728 --> 00:24:42,564
Mr. Kim, hello. Oh.

416
00:24:48,778 --> 00:24:50,864
Lastly, I know this is a bad time,

417
00:24:50,947 --> 00:24:53,742
but I really want to audition
for the main news show.

418
00:24:53,825 --> 00:24:55,702
The main news show? Are you kidding?

419
00:24:55,785 --> 00:24:57,662
Your name was taken off
the list ages ago.

420
00:24:58,371 --> 00:25:01,374
Are you dense or just thoughtless?

421
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:02,626
Get out, you moron!

422
00:25:03,543 --> 00:25:04,961
I'll make you pay for this.

423
00:25:05,587 --> 00:25:06,421
I swear.

424
00:25:07,214 --> 00:25:08,215
Make me pay?

425
00:25:09,799 --> 00:25:10,717
Ki-Baek.

426
00:25:12,469 --> 00:25:13,637
What are you doing?

427
00:25:18,141 --> 00:25:21,144
Hey, let him talk. Keep going.

428
00:25:21,228 --> 00:25:23,688
Say what? You swear you'll what?

429
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:25,857
I swear…

430
00:25:28,526 --> 00:25:30,445
I'm sorry. Oh?

431
00:25:30,528 --> 00:25:32,072
I'm sorry. Oh.

432
00:25:32,155 --> 00:25:33,156
Oh.

433
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:36,451
-I'm sorry.
-Oh.

434
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:42,916
Bye.

435
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:46,670
He's been acting like a lunatic
since he went on your show.

436
00:25:46,753 --> 00:25:48,546
What happened to him over there?

437
00:25:48,630 --> 00:25:51,591
Well, I'm not really sure,

438
00:25:51,675 --> 00:25:54,010
but he certainly seems a little weird…

439
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:55,095
Hey.

440
00:25:58,098 --> 00:25:59,015
Mr. Song Ki-baek.

441
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:06,564
I got home very safely last night,
thanks to you.

442
00:26:06,648 --> 00:26:08,650
Right, I'm glad.

443
00:26:08,733 --> 00:26:09,985
Hey, listen.

444
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:12,779
Did you see a doctor
after the electric shock?

445
00:26:13,363 --> 00:26:14,489
No.

446
00:26:14,572 --> 00:26:16,741
You said you've been feeling weird.

447
00:26:16,825 --> 00:26:19,619
Shouldn't you go see
a psychiatrist or a neurologist?

448
00:26:20,287 --> 00:26:24,416
People know who I am,
and I'm a little self-conscious.

449
00:26:24,499 --> 00:26:26,668
What kind of nonsense is that?

450
00:26:27,377 --> 00:26:29,129
This may be a serious problem.

451
00:26:29,212 --> 00:26:30,380
Let's go to the hospital.

452
00:26:30,463 --> 00:26:32,590
-No, I'm not going.
-For God's sake.

453
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:36,720
Come on. I'll buy you tonkatsu.

454
00:26:46,938 --> 00:26:48,815
He's the doctor
I tried to get on our show.

455
00:26:48,898 --> 00:26:51,776
He promised to keep things
as private as possible.

456
00:27:00,327 --> 00:27:01,578
Hello, doctor.

457
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:03,455
Have a seat.

458
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:07,000
Didn't we say we'd meet
at the outpatient clinic after lunchtime?

459
00:27:07,584 --> 00:27:10,920
I'm sorry. I'm trying not to be seen
by many people.

460
00:27:11,671 --> 00:27:13,840
Please go on and eat. There's no rush.

461
00:27:13,923 --> 00:27:15,008
Oh, right. Yeah.

462
00:27:16,426 --> 00:27:20,930
Can someone's personality change
after being electrocuted?

463
00:27:21,014 --> 00:27:24,642
Like I said on the phone,
I'll have to run some tests to be sure.

464
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:26,519
Don't worry about it until we know more.

465
00:27:26,603 --> 00:27:29,481
I got myself in trouble
before I could even start to worry.

466
00:27:30,273 --> 00:27:33,777
Wait a minute. You look familiar.
Is he… He is, right?

467
00:27:35,111 --> 00:27:38,281
See? I told you he'd still recognize me.

468
00:27:38,365 --> 00:27:39,532
-Yes, I'm--
-A singer.

469
00:27:39,616 --> 00:27:41,034
-Oh.
-Oh.

470
00:27:43,286 --> 00:27:44,287
A news anchor.

471
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:45,914
Wow, I'm embarrassed for you.

472
00:27:45,997 --> 00:27:47,665
That's why you looked so familiar.

473
00:27:48,416 --> 00:27:49,626
I'm a fan.

474
00:28:03,848 --> 00:28:05,266
One plus one is…

475
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:07,644
Five. Oh!

476
00:28:08,812 --> 00:28:09,729
I did it.

477
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:11,731
Oh, I did it.

478
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:13,441
I did it.

479
00:28:14,734 --> 00:28:17,987
This is all because of stress.
Stress is the cause.

480
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:21,491
I'm okay. I'm okay now.

481
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:26,371
Good morning, everyone.

482
00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:30,375
It's Wednesday, May 3rd,
and you're watching JBC Morning News.

483
00:28:30,458 --> 00:28:33,878
For the holidays in May, the Ministry
of Culture, Sports and Tourism…

484
00:28:33,962 --> 00:28:36,965
MCST ANNOUNCES NEW PLAN TO BOOST
CONSUMPTION FOR FAMILY MONTH

