00:30:23,822 --> 00:30:25,114
I'm here to cast you.

516
00:30:25,198 --> 00:30:28,034
Jeong-heon, I'd love to have you
on my new show.

517
00:30:28,117 --> 00:30:31,037
I told you to talk to Ms. Ma
about these things.

518
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:34,457
I'm not an idiot. You always have her
turn people down for you.

519
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:37,168
Who's your head writer?

520
00:30:37,252 --> 00:30:38,419
Oh, our head writer?

521
00:30:38,503 --> 00:30:39,796
She's really good.

522
00:30:39,879 --> 00:30:42,507
-It's Kim--
-No. Do you know Ms. On Woo-ju?

523
00:30:42,590 --> 00:30:43,925
She's great at her job.

524
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:46,928
Of course I know her.
I hear she really messed up her last show,

525
00:30:47,011 --> 00:30:48,471
and now she's planning a new one.

526
00:30:49,430 --> 00:30:50,473
She's planning a new show?

527
00:30:50,557 --> 00:30:52,392
Yeah, but it's literally just planning.

528
00:30:52,475 --> 00:30:54,477
Who knows if it will get off the ground?

529
00:30:54,561 --> 00:30:57,438
I doubt that it will,
seeing how incompetent she is.

530
00:30:57,522 --> 00:31:00,149
Our head writer, though,
always gets amazing ratings--

531
00:31:00,233 --> 00:31:01,234
Mr. Jang.

532
00:31:03,194 --> 00:31:04,863
-Are you close with Ms. On?
-No.

533
00:31:04,946 --> 00:31:06,906
So you're just rude then.

534
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,908
You talk about people behind their backs.

535
00:31:08,992 --> 00:31:10,702
I don't want to work with someone rude.

536
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:13,288
-Hyeong-taek, Mr. Jang is leaving.
-Yes?

537
00:31:14,038 --> 00:31:16,082
-Mr. Jang, let me walk you out.
-Wait, but…

538
00:31:16,165 --> 00:31:18,042
Have some deer antler extract.
I'll call you.

539
00:31:18,126 --> 00:31:20,336
-Oh, thanks.
-I hope you enjoy it. Bye!

540
00:31:21,170 --> 00:31:22,630
-Hyeong-taek.
-Yes?

541
00:31:22,714 --> 00:31:24,007
You know a lot of scriptwriters?

542
00:31:24,757 --> 00:31:26,426
Yes.

543
00:31:27,218 --> 00:31:28,386
This is actually better.

544
00:31:28,469 --> 00:31:30,263
We're in a corner room,
so we can focus.

545
00:31:30,889 --> 00:31:35,059
And the talent managers don't come here,
so we'll be left alone to focus.

546
00:31:35,143 --> 00:31:36,978
Those are all talent managers.

547
00:31:38,187 --> 00:31:39,230
I-na.

548
00:31:40,064 --> 00:31:43,276
I love how it's next to the smoking area
and there are no bugs.

549
00:31:43,359 --> 00:31:45,236
We're so close to the bathroom too.

550
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,405
I'll make sure we move somewhere far away

551
00:31:47,488 --> 00:31:49,282
from cigarette smoke and bathrooms.

552
00:31:49,365 --> 00:31:51,367
-Let's make our next show a hit, okay?
-Yeah.

553
00:31:52,619 --> 00:31:54,245
I suddenly had an idea yesterday.

554
00:31:54,329 --> 00:31:55,163
All right, check this out.

555
00:31:55,246 --> 00:31:56,998
Lots of celebrities live on Jeju Island.

556
00:31:57,081 --> 00:32:00,209
We could get some to Seoul
and compare their lives in the two places.

557
00:32:00,293 --> 00:32:01,920
Like coming back to the city.

558
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:03,129
What do you think?

559
00:32:03,838 --> 00:32:05,131
Seoul Check-In.

560
00:32:05,214 --> 00:32:06,090
What?

561
00:32:06,174 --> 00:32:09,052
I think Director Kim Tae-ho
already did that with Lee Hyo-ri.

562
00:32:09,677 --> 00:32:12,263
Hey, mine would feature more people.

563
00:32:12,347 --> 00:32:13,973
He only had Lee Hyo-ri.

564
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:17,393
Oh, it looked like Kim Jeong-heon
was looking for a new show to host.

565
00:32:17,477 --> 00:32:19,145
He wants to try something new.

566
00:32:19,228 --> 00:32:20,897
Oh, Kim Jeong-heon?

567
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:23,316
If we could cast him,
the show would be a hit for sure.

568
00:32:23,399 --> 00:32:24,859
Right?

569
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:27,028
He's not even that funny.

570
00:32:27,111 --> 00:32:29,822
No, he's really hot right now.

571
00:32:29,906 --> 00:32:33,242
I actually know his manager.
Should I ask about his schedule?

572
00:32:37,622 --> 00:32:38,915
I have an awards ceremony today.

573
00:32:38,998 --> 00:32:41,084
Oh. Did you win an award?

574
00:32:41,167 --> 00:32:44,003
I'm going so I win one in the future.
All the celebs will be there.

575
00:32:44,087 --> 00:32:46,506
I'll go hook them all in. Sparta!

576
00:32:46,589 --> 00:32:49,467
Ooh, ooh!
I-na, you said you'd say it together.

577
00:32:49,550 --> 00:32:51,052
Ooh, ooh.

578
00:32:54,097 --> 00:32:55,348
No freaking way.

579
00:32:55,431 --> 00:32:56,849
Oh, my gosh.

580
00:32:58,434 --> 00:33:00,103
Hello? Hi, Mr. Kang.

581
00:33:00,186 --> 00:33:03,231
You know, we were just talking
about Mr. Kim Jeong-heon.

582
00:33:05,274 --> 00:33:07,235
Here she comes. You look fabulous!

583
00:33:07,318 --> 00:33:10,488
All right. Thank you. Thank you, GVAN.

584
00:33:10,571 --> 00:33:13,574
Now, please welcome Kim Jeong-heon.

585
00:33:14,158 --> 00:33:16,202
It's like the David statue
has come to life.

586
00:33:16,285 --> 00:33:17,996
Doesn't he look dashing?

587
00:33:18,079 --> 00:33:19,080
Look over here, please.

588
00:33:19,163 --> 00:33:21,207
Please look to your left too.

589
00:33:21,290 --> 00:33:22,375
-That's cute.
-Over here!

590
00:33:22,458 --> 00:33:24,919
-Okay. Thank you, Jeong-heon.
-Thank you.

591
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:26,546
All right.

592
00:33:27,380 --> 00:33:30,008
This is a gift from Chairman Park Pil-gu
of Joa Tasty Rice.

593
00:33:30,091 --> 00:33:31,676
Jeong-heon, I'm a big fan.

594
00:33:31,759 --> 00:33:32,885
Oh, thank you.

595
00:33:33,469 --> 00:33:34,929
Thank you for the gift.

596
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:36,389
Come on.

597
00:33:36,472 --> 00:33:37,598
A rice cooker?

598
00:33:38,975 --> 00:33:40,393
Hang on.

599
00:33:41,144 --> 00:33:42,353
Please take some pictures!

600
00:33:42,437 --> 00:33:45,523
-I love Joa Tasty Rice!
-He looks stunning holding a rice cooker.

601
00:33:45,606 --> 00:33:47,025
Over here, please!

602
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:47,942
Yes!

603
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:49,861
-Please look over here.
-I love it!

604
00:33:49,944 --> 00:33:52,697
Isn't he the best? All right.

605
00:33:52,780 --> 00:33:54,866
And look, he's very strong too.

606
00:33:54,949 --> 00:33:58,202
Of course. Thank you, Jeong-heon.

607
00:33:58,286 --> 00:33:59,370
Thank you.

608
00:33:59,454 --> 00:34:01,456
You're not here to shoot an ad.
How embarrassing.

609
00:34:01,539 --> 00:34:04,250
Isn't embarrassment
better than losing a commercial?

610
00:34:04,333 --> 00:34:06,085
I lost my old rice cooker commercial,

611
00:34:06,169 --> 00:34:08,880
so I just got myself a new one.
Joa Tasty Rice!

612
00:34:11,507 --> 00:34:13,801
Hey, Hyeong-taek. Did you find out?

613
00:34:14,594 --> 00:34:15,762
A different show?

614
00:34:16,471 --> 00:34:18,306
Okay.

615
00:34:19,098 --> 00:34:21,934
No, it's nothing.
I'll call you later. Bye.

616
00:34:22,518 --> 00:34:24,395
Was that Mr. Kang? What is it?

617
00:34:25,354 --> 00:34:26,189
Well, kind of.

618
00:34:26,272 --> 00:34:28,441
"Kind of"?
You're acting suspiciously again.

619
00:34:28,524 --> 00:34:29,484
Can I go in now?

620
00:34:29,567 --> 00:34:31,736
-Yes, go ahead.
-Thank you.

621
00:34:33,404 --> 00:34:35,740
No, I haven't met Hey Meeny Miny Poe yet.

622
00:34:35,823 --> 00:34:37,909
You still haven't met her yet?

623
00:34:37,992 --> 00:34:39,535
-No.
-All right.

624
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:40,953
That's Lee Jeong-un.

625
00:34:42,288 --> 00:34:43,706
Hello.

626
00:34:43,790 --> 00:34:45,291
Sol, I just saw Lee Jeong-un.

627
00:34:45,374 --> 00:34:46,417
You don't know him?

628
00:34:46,501 --> 00:34:49,170
Anyway, I'll go inside
and look for her, okay?

629
00:34:49,253 --> 00:34:50,922
I'll call you later, honey. Bye.

630
00:34:52,215 --> 00:34:54,759
Hey. This event is hosted by our company,

631
00:34:54,842 --> 00:34:56,719
and the higher-ups are paying attention.

632
00:34:56,803 --> 00:35:00,264
If you do a good job here, I'm sure
Mr. Kim will give you another chance.

633
00:35:00,348 --> 00:35:01,599
Try not to be nervous.

634
00:35:01,682 --> 00:35:04,352
God, I'm so nervous. Aren't you nervous?

635
00:35:05,228 --> 00:35:06,270
Not at all.

636
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:08,231
Wow, impressive.

637
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:14,987
On Woo-ju.

638
00:35:24,956 --> 00:35:25,790
It's been a long time.

639
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:28,876
You're right.

640
00:35:30,002 --> 00:35:31,087
You look good.

641
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:37,260
-Are you--
-Ms. On Woo-ju?

642
00:35:38,136 --> 00:35:39,178
Oh.

643
00:35:39,262 --> 00:35:40,555
This is Director Ma Mi-ra.

644
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:43,141
I'm Ma Mi-ra.

645
00:35:43,808 --> 00:35:45,852
Are you close with Jeong-heon?

646
00:35:49,105 --> 00:35:49,939
No.

647
00:35:53,734 --> 00:35:54,819
Please excuse me.

648
00:35:59,282 --> 00:36:00,283
Mr. Song Ki-baek.

649
00:36:01,492 --> 00:36:02,493
What are you doing here?

650
00:36:02,577 --> 00:36:07,748
Oh, I am hosting the ceremony.

651
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:09,250
Oh.

652
00:36:10,376 --> 00:36:11,752
Song Ki-baek?

653
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:16,007
I heard you became an anchor.

654
00:36:16,090 --> 00:36:17,842
Good to see you. How have you been?

655
00:36:18,718 --> 00:36:19,552
Hey.

656
00:36:20,261 --> 00:36:22,805
Ji-hu, I've got to go change.
I'll catch you later.

657
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:23,890
All right.

658
00:36:25,266 --> 00:36:26,517
Wait, Woo-ju.

659
00:36:26,601 --> 00:36:28,644
Jeong-heon. I'm a fan.

660
00:36:28,728 --> 00:36:29,937
Can we take a picture?

661
00:36:32,648 --> 00:36:33,900
-Thank you.
-Sure.

662
00:36:33,983 --> 00:36:34,984
Awesome.

663
00:36:37,945 --> 00:36:40,239
THE 1ST KOREA BRAND AWARDS

664
00:37:03,512 --> 00:37:06,098
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

665
00:37:06,182 --> 00:37:09,977
I thank you for your creation
and cultivation of world-leading brands

666
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:13,105
that represent Korea
in various fields of business.

667
00:37:13,689 --> 00:37:18,027
It's such an honor to host
the first Korea Brand Awards.

668
00:37:18,110 --> 00:37:20,821
I am Anchor Song Ki-baek of JBC.

669
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:28,496
HOTTEST ICON OF THE YEAR

670
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:31,457
And now, we move on to the award
for the Hottest Icon of the Year.

671
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:35,503
Here to present is Chairman Park Seong-jae
of Toto Olleh Chicken.

672
00:37:35,586 --> 00:37:37,088
Please welcome him with a big hand.

673
00:37:37,171 --> 00:37:39,006
TOTO OLLEH
1 MILLION WON GIFT CERTIFICATE

674
00:37:39,882 --> 00:37:42,802
Now, let's find out
who the nominees are.

675
00:37:44,971 --> 00:37:47,723
ONLINE SECTOR
HOTTEST ICON OF THE YEAR

676
00:37:48,307 --> 00:37:51,727
Ki-baek, your face looks a bit oily,
so let's put some powder on it.

677
00:37:52,436 --> 00:37:56,274
You guys are doing this because
I'm nice to you and do what you ask me to.

678
00:37:56,357 --> 00:37:58,609
Today, I'm a bit…

679
00:38:16,210 --> 00:38:20,047
These are the nominees
for the Hottest Icon of the Year.

680
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:23,050
With the rise of K-content
to new heights this year,

681
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:26,178
the competition is expected
to be extremely fierce.

682
00:38:26,262 --> 00:38:27,888
Who will win this award?
It's pretty obvious.

683
00:38:28,472 --> 00:38:29,307
What?

684
00:38:34,228 --> 00:38:38,816
Who will win this fierce competition
and claim this honorable award?

685
00:38:38,899 --> 00:38:40,985
Only one of the nominees
is here tonight.

686
00:38:48,284 --> 00:38:51,162
For a small awards show like this,
only the winners show up.

687
00:38:58,919 --> 00:39:01,255
The winner is Park Se-mi. Congratulations.

688
00:39:13,684 --> 00:39:17,438
Park Se-mi is a comedian
who's widely known as Seo-jun's mom,

689
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:20,524
who is a character she plays
on her beloved YouTube channel.

690
00:39:20,608 --> 00:39:23,235
Congratulations on your award again.

691
00:39:28,199 --> 00:39:31,744
I'm sure you didn't give me this award
just because I'm the only one present.

692
00:39:33,954 --> 00:39:35,915
Ki-baek, what are you doing?

693
00:39:35,998 --> 00:39:37,666
You're ad-libbing too much.

694
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,377
Ad-libbing? Are you kidding?

695
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:40,878
What did you just say?

696
00:39:40,961 --> 00:39:42,004
No, no.

697
00:39:44,507 --> 00:39:46,217
Mr. Song, are you all right?

698
00:39:47,510 --> 00:39:49,553
I don't think I can do this anymore.

699
00:39:49,637 --> 00:39:50,596
What?

700
00:39:50,679 --> 00:39:52,515
Mr. Song. Please go back up onstage.

701
00:39:52,598 --> 00:39:54,642
I'm in no condition
to host the show right now.

702
00:39:54,725 --> 00:39:56,685
Stop talking nonsense and get up there.

703
00:39:56,769 --> 00:39:58,312
-No, but--
-Just go.

704
00:39:58,396 --> 00:39:59,730
-Get up there.
-No, I really--

705
00:39:59,814 --> 00:40:01,190
Ki-baek is going back onstage.

706
00:40:01,273 --> 00:40:02,149
Stand by.

707
00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:07,780
This is insulting.

708
00:40:10,908 --> 00:40:12,493
-Seriously.
-Oh, my word.

709
00:40:12,576 --> 00:40:15,746
All right. Let's move on
to the next award.

710
00:40:15,830 --> 00:40:19,333
The next category is
Best Sports-Entertainer of the Year.

711
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:21,252
Boy, this is the 19th award already.

712
00:40:21,877 --> 00:40:23,629
I'll be presenting the award myself.

713
00:40:23,712 --> 00:40:25,714
This is not a major award, so…

714
00:40:27,508 --> 00:40:29,093
Kim Seung-hyeon, congratulations.

715
00:40:31,053 --> 00:40:32,596
BEST SPORTS-ENTERTAINER
OF THE YEAR

716
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:34,557
Let's give him a big round of applause.

717
00:40:49,822 --> 00:40:51,740
I have a lot of people to thank.

718
00:40:53,284 --> 00:40:55,786
-Heo Su-min of Ungok Entertainment.
-Tell him to keep it short.

719
00:40:55,870 --> 00:40:56,829
Lee Jae-yong--

720
00:40:56,912 --> 00:41:02,209
Oh, the staff just asked to make
the speech short and straightforward,

721
00:41:02,293 --> 00:41:05,045
but you're the ones
who decided to present 19 awards.

722
00:41:06,964 --> 00:41:08,257
Feel free to finish.

723
00:41:12,970 --> 00:41:14,054
Director Kim Hong-jun,

724
00:41:14,138 --> 00:41:18,809
Manager Choi Ja-yeong,
Director Kim Geun-u, Director Lee Eun-ha,

725
00:41:18,893 --> 00:41:23,022
Manager Kim Seon-jun, CEO Jang Ji-yeon
of Hair Boutique Gangnam--

726
00:41:23,105 --> 00:41:25,065
That's going to take forever.

727
00:41:25,149 --> 00:41:27,568
Why does everyone thank
such a long list of people?

728
00:41:27,651 --> 00:41:29,862
If you want to thank someone,
do it whenever you can.

729
00:41:38,913 --> 00:41:40,623
I'll keep working hard. Thank you.

730
00:41:41,832 --> 00:41:44,877
Congratulations!

731
00:41:45,836 --> 00:41:46,962
Congratulations!

732
00:41:48,631 --> 00:41:49,715
Unbelievable.

733
00:41:53,677 --> 00:41:55,429
Carry on.

734
00:41:58,516 --> 00:42:00,976
There's still an award left.
Best Actor of the Year.

735
00:42:03,270 --> 00:42:08,609
Presenting the award is
Chairman Park Pil-gu of Joa Tasty Rice.

736
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:10,319
Let's welcome him with a big hand.

737
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:12,780
BEST ACTOR OF THE YEAR

738
00:42:12,863 --> 00:42:15,241
Greetings. Well, may I announce…

739
00:42:16,617 --> 00:42:19,286
Right, okay.
I'll announce the winner then.

740
00:42:19,370 --> 00:42:22,373
The first Korea Brand Awards.

741
00:42:22,456 --> 00:42:26,835
Best Actor of the Year goes
to Lee Jeong-un. Congratulations.

742
00:42:28,045 --> 00:42:30,798
Let's give it up for him. Congratulations.

743
00:42:34,677 --> 00:42:39,390
Lee Jeong-un came back from
a long hiatus to play Kim Man-ho,

744
00:42:39,473 --> 00:42:43,561
the drug king who dominates the world
of darkness, in last year's film Junkers.

745
00:42:43,644 --> 00:42:47,815
Ironically, the reason he went on hiatus
was because of his alleged drug use.

746
00:42:51,527 --> 00:42:53,988
Drugs became his downfall
and his redemption.

747
00:42:54,071 --> 00:42:56,198
He's the true drug king of our time.

748
00:42:56,282 --> 00:42:58,659
I'm sorry!

749
00:43:38,282 --> 00:43:39,283
Ki-baek.

750
00:43:39,825 --> 00:43:41,076
Song Ki-baek!

751
00:43:41,577 --> 00:43:42,620
Hey!

752
00:43:43,537 --> 00:43:46,582
-What?
-Hey, are you okay?

753
00:43:46,665 --> 00:43:49,501
Oh, Mr. Kim.

754
00:43:50,711 --> 00:43:53,047
Things could've gone
a lot worse, you know.

755
00:43:54,089 --> 00:43:57,509
Mr. Kim. I'm sorry.

756
00:43:57,593 --> 00:43:59,136
Come on, it's okay.

757
00:43:59,219 --> 00:44:02,848
You just messed up
a stupid awards show. It's not a big deal.

758
00:44:04,433 --> 00:44:07,936
Don't let something like this
get you down.

759
00:44:08,687 --> 00:44:10,356
Go back to how you were earlier.

760
00:44:11,065 --> 00:44:12,107
Sir?

761
00:44:12,191 --> 00:44:15,778
You had a lot of nerve
running your mouth like that.

762
00:44:16,362 --> 00:44:17,279
I…

763
00:44:17,905 --> 00:44:20,616
-Go ahead and say whatever you want.
-No, I…

764
00:44:20,699 --> 00:44:23,869
I can always find another news anchor.

765
00:44:23,952 --> 00:44:27,498
What's the point of good qualifications,
a good family, and a nice image?

766
00:44:27,581 --> 00:44:29,375
It's all meaningless.

767
00:44:29,958 --> 00:44:32,294
They're all fake.

768
00:44:42,221 --> 00:44:43,472
Mom.

769
00:44:43,555 --> 00:44:44,515
What are you doing here?

770
00:44:44,598 --> 00:44:46,975
What does it look like?
I'm working, of course.

771
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:50,521
I've got to earn every penny I can.
Am I right?

772
00:44:55,275 --> 00:44:57,569
Sweetheart, I know you've had a long day.

773
00:44:59,154 --> 00:44:59,988
Mom.

774
00:45:01,615 --> 00:45:02,991
My perfect son.

775
00:45:03,075 --> 00:45:04,743
You did nothing wrong, okay?

776
00:45:04,827 --> 00:45:07,329
It's not like you hit or killed someone.

777
00:45:07,413 --> 00:45:09,456
You said a few things
that were on your mind.

778
00:45:09,540 --> 00:45:11,250
What's wrong with that?

779
00:45:14,294 --> 00:45:16,130
Just lie to people again, honey.

780
00:45:16,213 --> 00:45:17,965
You're good at that.

781
00:45:18,048 --> 00:45:21,009
You have to keep pretending
like we don't exist

782
00:45:21,093 --> 00:45:24,805
and continue living a facade
as the perfect Song Ki-baek

783
00:45:24,888 --> 00:45:28,767
so we can sponge off you forever. Right?

784
00:45:30,477 --> 00:45:31,478
Mom.

785
00:45:48,912 --> 00:45:50,539
I thought his family was well-off.

786
00:45:50,622 --> 00:45:53,834
I heard you'd make the finance section
if your house were to be revealed.

787
00:45:53,917 --> 00:45:56,128
They say he comes
from a powerful family.

788
00:45:56,211 --> 00:45:58,422
So he's not the prince but the pauper.

789
00:45:58,505 --> 00:46:01,258
Says who?
You're the ones who created my image.

790
00:46:01,341 --> 00:46:03,427
It takes skills to build a good image!

791
00:46:03,510 --> 00:46:06,680
He's been acting like he's got it all
and like he's a good person.

792
00:46:06,763 --> 00:46:10,392
Man, it's unbelievable.
It's all been complete lies.

793
00:46:12,811 --> 00:46:14,480
I have to ask him for money today.

794
00:46:14,563 --> 00:46:16,982
Can I ask for just another 100,000 won?

795
00:46:17,065 --> 00:46:19,318
Let's sit down and talk.

796
00:46:44,593 --> 00:46:49,139
Huh? What… What's that?

797
00:47:15,123 --> 00:47:15,958
What?

798
00:47:35,060 --> 00:47:36,061
Huh?

799
00:47:42,359 --> 00:47:43,235
What happened?

800
00:47:44,528 --> 00:47:45,362
44 UNREAD MESSAGES

801
00:47:47,114 --> 00:47:48,073
POSITION: NEWS DIVISION
NAME: SONG KI-BAEK

802
00:47:48,156 --> 00:47:49,825
Song Ki-baek is being penalized.

803
00:47:50,701 --> 00:47:52,119
You know, I'm worried.

804
00:47:53,078 --> 00:47:54,329
About what?

805
00:47:54,413 --> 00:47:55,872
About Song Ki-baek.

806
00:47:55,956 --> 00:47:59,001
What if something really
happened to him in that accident?

807
00:47:59,084 --> 00:48:00,043
What accident?

808
00:48:02,588 --> 00:48:03,630
On Woo-ju.

809
00:48:05,215 --> 00:48:07,301
Oh, Ms. Chae. It's been a while.

810
00:48:07,384 --> 00:48:08,260
Hi.

811
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:10,554
What's going on?

812
00:48:10,637 --> 00:48:13,056
Well, I was just in the neighborhood,

813
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:16,810
and I thought I'd stop by
your mom's hair salon.

814
00:48:18,604 --> 00:48:20,022
Go play with your grandma, okay?

815
00:48:21,189 --> 00:48:22,232
Go ahead, Yeon.

816
00:48:24,151 --> 00:48:25,444
-Bye.
-Bye.

817
00:48:30,407 --> 00:48:31,408
Want to grab a coffee?

818
00:48:31,491 --> 00:48:33,702
I sent Yeon away
because I thought you'd do this.

819
00:48:34,745 --> 00:48:35,746
Let's go.

820
00:48:35,829 --> 00:48:37,748
Just leave. I have somewhere to be.

821
00:48:38,373 --> 00:48:40,709
I sent her away
because I didn't want to embarrass you.

822
00:48:42,252 --> 00:48:43,462
Goodbye.

823
00:49:01,521 --> 00:49:02,356
What?

824
00:49:04,024 --> 00:49:05,567
What's going on?

825
00:49:08,528 --> 00:49:09,571
Oh…

826
00:49:18,372 --> 00:49:21,416
Don't you get clingy too, Beep Beep.

827
00:49:22,417 --> 00:49:23,543
God, this is embarrassing.

828
00:49:23,627 --> 00:49:27,923
Embarrassing? I love this car.
Why is it embarrassing?

829
00:49:28,006 --> 00:49:29,591
It's a used car for one thing,

830
00:49:29,675 --> 00:49:32,052
and I spent the money
I saved for your birthday gift.

831
00:49:32,135 --> 00:49:34,346
That's what makes it more meaningful.

832
00:49:34,429 --> 00:49:36,515
That means I own a small part of it.

833
00:49:39,309 --> 00:49:40,727
Oh, this is great.

834
00:49:40,811 --> 00:49:44,314
Now you don't have to stay all night
at bus terminals to make morning shoots,

835
00:49:44,398 --> 00:49:46,400
and you have a place to be
when you're on standby.

836
00:49:46,483 --> 00:49:48,694
And we can go somewhere far together.

837
00:49:48,777 --> 00:49:49,736
That's right.

838
00:49:51,947 --> 00:49:55,075
Please keep him safe, Beep Beep. Okay?

839
00:49:55,158 --> 00:49:56,284
You named it Beep Beep?

840
00:49:56,368 --> 00:49:57,452
Yeah, Beep Beep.

841
00:49:59,121 --> 00:50:01,331
It's the assistant director.

842
00:50:01,415 --> 00:50:02,582
Hello, sir.

843
00:50:02,666 --> 00:50:05,460
Oh, I'm on my way now. Yes.

844
00:50:05,544 --> 00:50:08,380
Sorry? Liquid painkiller?

845
00:50:08,964 --> 00:50:10,757
I don't have a liquid painkiller.

846
00:50:11,717 --> 00:50:13,969
Oh, no. I'll get you one.

847
00:50:14,052 --> 00:50:16,638
Yes. Don't worry. Bye.

848
00:50:17,222 --> 00:50:20,809
We're in the middle of nowhere.
How are we going to find a pharmacy?

849
00:50:20,892 --> 00:50:21,893
Ta-da!

850
00:50:23,270 --> 00:50:25,397
There's a pharmacy right here.
How do you…

851
00:50:25,480 --> 00:50:27,858
What, never been bitten
by mosquitoes at a shoot?

852
00:50:29,234 --> 00:50:31,278
Oh, Jeong-heon. Stop!

853
00:50:31,361 --> 00:50:32,404
What? Oh!

854
00:50:33,029 --> 00:50:35,115
TASTY DUMPLINGS AND STEAMED BUNS

855
00:50:35,198 --> 00:50:37,325
Hello. Could I have a box of steamed buns?

856
00:50:37,409 --> 00:50:38,827
-All right.
-Thank you.

857
00:50:38,910 --> 00:50:40,370
Sure, please enjoy.

858
00:50:41,955 --> 00:50:43,081
Are you hungry?

859
00:50:43,915 --> 00:50:47,169
The FDs accidentally sat on a bag of buns
they were going to use,

860
00:50:47,252 --> 00:50:49,379
and Yeong-gyu saw it.
He's refusing to eat them.

861
00:50:49,463 --> 00:50:52,174
But how did you even catch that?

862
00:50:52,257 --> 00:50:54,926
Wow. It's insane how quickly you think.

863
00:50:55,010 --> 00:50:58,972
They call me the super rookie
for a reason.

864
00:50:59,639 --> 00:51:00,515
Let's go.

865
00:51:02,309 --> 00:51:03,351
Come on, let's go.

866
00:51:19,367 --> 00:51:21,119
It can be described as disinhibition.

867
00:51:21,203 --> 00:51:24,664
The lesion in your brain has caused
emotional dysregulation

868
00:51:24,748 --> 00:51:28,418
and personality changes
similar to symptoms of dementia.

869
00:51:28,502 --> 00:51:30,212
But there's no danger to your life.

870
00:51:30,295 --> 00:51:33,673
Nonetheless, considering your job,

871
00:51:33,757 --> 00:51:38,345
being unable to control the things you say
could be a challenging issue for you.

872
00:51:48,897 --> 00:51:50,565
Hey. How are you?

873
00:51:52,484 --> 00:51:53,902
Move out of the apartment?

874
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:55,445
It's a little unexpected.

875
00:51:56,780 --> 00:51:58,198
You're moving back next month?

876
00:51:58,782 --> 00:52:00,659
You said I could stay
as long as I wanted.

877
00:52:01,243 --> 00:52:02,077
I mean…

878
00:52:02,994 --> 00:52:05,038
I don't have money
to get a place right now.

879
00:52:06,248 --> 00:52:08,834
It's your apartment.
You can do whatever you want with it.

880
00:52:10,836 --> 00:52:13,505
Your car is fine too.
Listen, I have to go.

881
00:52:32,023 --> 00:52:34,860
Min-gu, all the locations
on your list looked great.

882
00:52:34,943 --> 00:52:37,571
The Fishermen and the Country shot there.
They said it was amazing.

883
00:52:37,654 --> 00:52:40,490
I should've come with you.
I'm really sorry, Woo-ju.

884
00:52:41,074 --> 00:52:42,158
Don't worry about it.

885
00:52:42,242 --> 00:52:44,494
I can check out these locations by myself.

886
00:52:44,578 --> 00:52:45,996
I'll talk to you later. Bye.

887
00:52:46,079 --> 00:52:47,205
-Okay.
-Bye.

888
00:52:48,415 --> 00:52:50,041
Wow, this place looks fantastic.

889
00:52:56,798 --> 00:52:58,008
Hey, isn't this nice?

890
00:52:59,759 --> 00:53:00,927
Aren't you glad you came?

891
00:53:02,095 --> 00:53:03,179
It's nice.

892
00:53:04,014 --> 00:53:07,809
It took me a lot of effort to join
The Fishermen and the Country, you know.

893
00:53:08,810 --> 00:53:10,520
I should practice my fishing technique.

894
00:53:11,187 --> 00:53:12,981
That rock is a good fishing spot.

895
00:53:13,815 --> 00:53:14,774
Yeah?

896
00:53:15,817 --> 00:53:18,028
There are a lot of things I want to ask,

897
00:53:18,612 --> 00:53:20,030
but we're here to have fun today,

898
00:53:20,780 --> 00:53:22,490
so let's do that.
Talk to me when you're ready.

899
00:53:23,074 --> 00:53:24,034
Yeah.

900
00:53:25,201 --> 00:53:27,120
I'll catch you some black sea bream.

901
00:53:28,121 --> 00:53:30,916
FISHING EXPERIENCE

902
00:53:56,942 --> 00:53:58,318
Oh, you're adorable.

903
00:53:58,401 --> 00:54:00,570
This is supposed to be a good spot,

904
00:54:00,654 --> 00:54:02,530
so why can't I catch a single minnow?

905
00:54:02,614 --> 00:54:04,658
Even the god of the sea
couldn't get you one.

906
00:54:04,741 --> 00:54:07,369
Minnows live in freshwater,
not in the ocean.

907
00:54:07,452 --> 00:54:11,289
Touché. Fishing is all about waiting.

908
00:54:11,373 --> 00:54:13,708
Aren't you supposed to be
the symbol of patience?

909
00:54:13,792 --> 00:54:15,085
Don't be ridiculous.

910
00:54:15,168 --> 00:54:16,878
Symbol of patience, my ass.

911
00:54:18,713 --> 00:54:20,006
You've been acting strange!

912
00:54:20,090 --> 00:54:21,383
You've changed. You know that?

913
00:54:23,301 --> 00:54:25,887
I'm going to go get something to drink.

914
00:54:25,971 --> 00:54:27,263
My butt's too sore to sit here.

915
00:54:30,767 --> 00:54:32,435
He's so touchy these days.

916
00:54:32,519 --> 00:54:34,187
-Thank you.
-Bye.

917
00:54:48,994 --> 00:54:51,371
Seriously, I'm not getting any bites.

918
00:54:53,456 --> 00:54:54,624
Hi, honey.

919
00:54:57,210 --> 00:55:00,046
What? But she was fine until this morning.

920
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:02,966
Damn it. Okay.
I'll be there as soon as I can.

921
00:55:09,055 --> 00:55:10,098
Good God.

922
00:55:11,975 --> 00:55:15,437
Damn it, I should've worn sneakers.

923
00:55:25,864 --> 00:55:27,532
Thank you for your cooperation.

924
00:55:27,615 --> 00:55:28,950
I'll be in touch.

925
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:39,502
Huh? What?

926
00:55:41,296 --> 00:55:42,797
Isn't that Song Ki-baek?

927
00:55:43,381 --> 00:55:45,925
What's he doing over there alone?

928
00:56:10,283 --> 00:56:12,285
Everything isn't over yet, right?

929
00:56:14,454 --> 00:56:15,955
Maybe it's already over.

930
00:56:19,042 --> 00:56:21,336
What is the matter with you, Ki-baek?

931
00:56:23,213 --> 00:56:25,799
What did I do
to deserve something like this?

932
00:56:25,882 --> 00:56:28,051
I've worked so hard to get here.

933
00:56:28,760 --> 00:56:29,677
Huh?

934
00:56:40,438 --> 00:56:42,941
Man, it's so damn beautiful.

935
00:56:47,570 --> 00:56:49,697
I'm really scared here.

936
00:56:52,158 --> 00:56:53,618
What's he doing up there?

937
00:57:05,630 --> 00:57:07,090
Mr. Song Ki-baek!

938
00:57:08,383 --> 00:57:10,093
Boy, now I'm even hearing things.

939
00:57:11,261 --> 00:57:14,264
Hey, stop! Stop!

940
00:57:16,182 --> 00:57:17,934
Huh? Ms. On?

941
00:57:18,017 --> 00:57:20,228
Just calm down and get down here.

942
00:57:20,311 --> 00:57:21,980
I know it's hard, but don't do this!

943
00:57:22,063 --> 00:57:24,190
Wait, what are you doing here?

944
00:57:24,274 --> 00:57:26,151
Everything is going to be okay.

945
00:57:26,234 --> 00:57:27,944
Come down here. Come on!

946
00:57:28,570 --> 00:57:31,322
Did you follow me here? Why?

947
00:57:33,324 --> 00:57:34,617
Why are you coming up here?

948
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:38,371
I know you're stronger
than this, Mr. Song!

949
00:57:39,205 --> 00:57:41,124
Don't come up here! It's dangerous!

950
00:57:41,624 --> 00:57:44,210
If you're feeling upset about something,
talk to me.

951
00:57:44,294 --> 00:57:45,587
I'll listen, okay?

952
00:57:45,670 --> 00:57:47,297
Listen to what? I told you.

953
00:57:47,380 --> 00:57:49,299
I'm not entirely fine!

954
00:57:50,383 --> 00:57:51,676
This is driving me crazy.

955
00:57:51,759 --> 00:57:53,344
Why are you doing this?

956
00:57:53,428 --> 00:57:54,512
Stop talking to me!

957
00:57:54,596 --> 00:57:56,764
This wouldn't have happened
if I hadn't met you.

958
00:57:56,848 --> 00:57:59,058
Why do you keep showing up in front of me?

959
00:57:59,142 --> 00:58:00,602
I said, don't come up here!

960
00:58:00,685 --> 00:58:02,312
Don't! Oh.

961
00:58:02,395 --> 00:58:04,397
Don't come near me. Just don't, okay?

962
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:08,735
Look, Mr. Song. Calm down. It's dangerous!

963
00:58:08,818 --> 00:58:11,529
-Get out of my sight!
-You'll fall!

964
00:58:11,613 --> 00:58:14,491
Oh, for God's sake.
Why would you follow me here?

965
00:58:14,574 --> 00:58:16,618
Oh, no! Don't move!

966
00:58:16,701 --> 00:58:18,578
Don't come near me!
Get out of my sight!

967
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:19,746
You'll fall!

968
00:58:57,909 --> 00:58:59,661
FRANKLY SPEAKING

969
00:59:00,453 --> 00:59:02,580
Have you gone totally insane? Get a grip!

970
00:59:02,664 --> 00:59:03,873
Help!

971
00:59:03,957 --> 00:59:07,085
When I see your face,
I get this strong feeling of…

972
00:59:07,168 --> 00:59:08,044
I feel better now.

973
00:59:08,127 --> 00:59:10,171
Ms. On, I hear you're having a hard time.

974
00:59:10,255 --> 00:59:12,507
Hey. Could you help me, please?

975
00:59:12,590 --> 00:59:16,010
I'm genuinely interested
in your new show as a show host.

976
00:59:16,094 --> 00:59:18,304
Just go. I'm not interested.

977
00:59:18,972 --> 00:59:21,015
I have a problem staying calm.

978
00:59:21,099 --> 00:59:24,185
Who invited Song Ki-baek here?
This is just embarrassing.

979
00:59:24,269 --> 00:59:26,646
What if the switch turns on
when I'm at work?

980
00:59:28,022 --> 00:59:29,983
You came to work? You've got thick skin.

981
00:59:31,859 --> 00:59:34,028
The switch is turned on, isn't it?

982
00:59:36,197 --> 00:59:40,201
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.
Welcome to JBC News.

983
00:59:52,130 --> 00:59:53,423
Aren't you scared?

984
00:59:55,216 --> 00:59:58,469
My mom said there's a shark in there.

985
00:59:59,095 --> 01:00:00,054
There's no shark.

986
01:00:00,138 --> 01:00:02,974
Your mom lied so you wouldn't spend
too much time in cold water.

987
01:00:03,057 --> 01:00:06,728
Also, when you grow up,
things like sharks don't scare you.

988
01:00:06,811 --> 01:00:09,647
What scares you is life.

989
01:00:15,653 --> 01:00:19,282
-Cold, isn't it?
-No, it's not cold at all.

990
01:00:19,907 --> 01:00:20,783
You're lying.

991
01:00:20,867 --> 01:00:23,077
I'm not lying.

992
01:00:24,454 --> 01:00:26,205
Aren't you cold?

993
01:00:26,289 --> 01:00:27,248
Nope.

994
01:00:28,166 --> 01:00:30,918
Are you the kind of grown-up
who never lies?

995
01:00:35,340 --> 01:00:37,300
Somehow, that's what I've become.

996
01:00:40,970 --> 01:00:43,431
Oh, it's really quiet.

997
01:00:44,182 --> 01:00:45,141
That's cool.

998
01:00:48,770 --> 01:00:50,480
It's not cool. It's ruining me.

999
01:00:51,189 --> 01:00:53,107
People might say it's cool.

1000
01:00:54,067 --> 01:00:59,656
Or that it's satisfying without realizing
how it's completely messing up my life.

1001
01:01:00,531 --> 01:01:02,367
Hey, can we be friends?

1002
01:01:03,618 --> 01:01:07,455
I have a feeling something fun will happen
if I'm with you.

1003
01:01:08,414 --> 01:01:09,957
I'm not sure.

1004
